-- Japanese Bought Net 428.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2012-12-27T23:53:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-27/japanese-bought-net-428-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Dec. 21 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 428.2 billion yen ($5.0 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 231.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 100.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 96.5 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 850.9 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 764.9 billion yen in stocks, and sold 402.4 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 488.3
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
